Dear Hiring Team,

I am a Computer Science student at Curtin University, focused on building full-stack systems and backend services. Canva is the standard I build towards.

I have designed and shipped full-stack applications end-to-end, building backend services that handle real-world workloads and integrating them with user-facing systems. This includes developing asynchronous processing systems in Go for high-volume document workflows, designing APIs to support frontend-backend integration, and deploying applications to production environments on AWS. I’ve also built systems that prioritise performance and low-latency interactions, ensuring they scale reliably in practice.

Alongside this, I’ve worked on production systems in a distributed environment, collaborating with engineers to develop backend features, contribute to system design, and improve overall performance and reliability. I am comfortable in JavaScript, TypeScript, Python, and Go, with strong foundations in object-oriented programming and system design.

I’m particularly interested in working on backend systems that operate at scale and directly impact users. Canva’s ability to deliver fast, reliable experiences to millions of users is exactly the kind of engineering I want to be part of.

Austin Delic
